full_text: A final audit is scheduled for workers' compensation or general liability policies in the base application. A final audit contains the verified, ultimate cost for a policy with variable basis. Login as an underwriter. In this example, the underwriter issued a general liability policy. The audit schedules are managed on its own page under Tools. The underwriter role does not have permissions to work with audits. Therefore, the action column does not have buttons visible. Note down the policy number. Log out. The auditors normally work with the audits. Login as Adam Auditor. Go to the same policy. Type in the policy number. Click the search icon. Go to the audit schedules page. In the action column, the edit button are visible for audits not yet started. The auditor can change the start date, due date, audit method, etc. The audit task batch process starts audit jobs when it is on, or passes the audit start date. Once the audit job is started, the auditor can view, and enter audit information. In this example, it has not reached the start date, so the audit job is not started. Log out. Log in as an auditor supervisor, who has the permission to manually start audit jobs. Locate the same policy. Go to audit schedules. In the action column, the edit, start, and wait buttons are visible. Manually start the final audit. There is a link to the audit job, which is available to users with the auditor role, as well. Clicking the link opens the audit wizard. Go to the details page. Enter the audited basis for the class code. Calculate the premium. Submit the final audit. Return to the policy. Go to audit schedules. Click the filter drop-down. To view the completed audits, select the option All, or Closed within last 12 months. The revise button is visible for completed final audits. It reverses the original final audit and copies the audit information to a new final audit. New information can be entered. Calculate the premium. Submit the revised final audit. This is the end of demonstration for final audit. This is the end of demonstration for final audit.
